05/06/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Prime Minister and Social Democratic Alliance of Macedonia (SDSM) leader Branko Crvenkovski met with Nikola Gruevski, the new chairman of the opposition VMRO-DPMNE, on Wednesday (4 June). The two agreed to restore normal communications between the ruling party and the opposition and to co-operate on issues concerning key national interests. They also reviewed progress in the implementation of the Ohrid Peace Accord, the implementation of the stand-by agreement with the IMF and other economic projects.
In other news, Crvenkovski denied that a rift has developed in the ruling coalition, and rejected rumours that the Democratic Union for Integration is threatening to leave the cabinet. After the SDSM Central Board session Tuesday evening, the prime minister said that relations within the coalition are not based on threats, but on mutual understanding. (Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik - 05/06/03; MIA, A1 TV - 04/06/03)
